HEADWORD: Lixivited
<hw>Lix*iv"i*`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Lixivium</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to lye or lixivium; of the quality of
alkaline salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Impregnated with salts from wood ashes.</def>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lixiviate</ent>⟦br⟧
